 President to felicitate achievers
OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT Anand will be present with cricketers, footballers and hockey players  New Delhi: Indias success in different disciplines in recent times has caught the attention of the upper echelons. According to a sports ministry source, the government is planning a joint felicitation for cricketers, footballers, hockey players and Viswanathan Anand at the Rashtrapati Bhavan next week. Those who will be felicitated are the World Twenty20 champions, the Asia Cup-winning hockey team, the Nehru Cup football champions and world chess champion Anand. President Pratibha Patil, it was learnt, will personally felicitate all the sportspersons. Contacted by The Telegraph, AIFF secretary Alberto Colaco said: We have been verbally told about the function, there has been no official intimation yet. The AIFF, however, has already made arrangements for the footballers to rush to Delhi after playing the World Cup qualifiers against Lebanon in Chennai on Sunday. According to a team source, the footballers will arrive in Delhi on Monday. The Rashtrapati Bhavan function is likely to be held on Sunday or Monday. 
